    <string name="how_intro">Learn the full game flow in under a minute.</string>
    <string name="how_objective_title">Objective</string>
    <string name="how_objective_line_1">All players except one see the same secret word.</string>
    <string name="how_objective_line_2">One player is the impostor and does not know the word.</string>
    <string name="how_objective_line_3">The group must find the impostor. The impostor must blend in and guess the word.</string>
    <string name="how_preparation_title">Preparation</string>
    <string name="how_preparation_line_1">Choose player count and categories to prepare the game.</string>
    <string name="how_preparation_line_2">The app assigns roles using one shared phone.</string>
    <string name="how_preparation_line_3">Each player checks in private, then passes the phone.</string>
    <string name="how_play_title">How the round works</string>
    <string name="how_play_line_1">Once everyone has seen their role, leave the phone aside.</string>
    <string name="how_play_line_2">In each round, every player says exactly 1 word related to the secret word.</string>
    <string name="how_play_line_3">A good default is 2 rounds before voting; add a third only if the group needs more information.</string>
    <string name="how_play_line_4">The app does not control spoken turns; the group does.</string>
    <string name="how_win_title">How to win</string>
    <string name="how_win_line_1">After 2 rounds, or 3 if your group still needs more information, vote for who you think is the impostor.</string>
    <string name="how_win_line_2">If the group catches the impostor, civilians win.</string>
    <string name="how_win_line_3">If the group misses, the impostor wins.</string>
    <string name="how_win_line_4">Optional house rule: if caught, the impostor may draw by guessing the word (not enforced by the app).</string>
    <string name="how_tips_title">Tips to play better</string>
    <string name="how_tip_1">Do not make your clue too obvious.</string>
    <string name="how_tip_2">2 rounds is usually the best starting point; add a third only if the group needs more information.</string>
    <string name="how_tip_3">Watch how others react and answer.</string>

